      <section id="marketing_cloud_interface">
        <title>
          <keyword>Marketing Cloud</keyword> 15.1.1</title>
        <p>New features and fixes in the 
			 <keyword>Adobe Marketing Cloud</keyword> collaboration and sharing
			 interface. 
		  </p>
        <draft-comment>
          <p>https://wiki.corp.adobe.com/display/marketingcloud/MC15.2.1+Release+Checklist
				
			 </p>
        </draft-comment>
        <table id="table_4E4B34EEE3D94D78BA1A1FBC62950559">
          <tgroup cols="2">
            <colspec colnum="1" colname="col1" colwidth="1.00*" />
            <colspec colnum="2" colname="col2" colwidth="1.75*" />
            <thead>
              <row>
                <entry colname="col1">Feature 
					 </entry>
                <entry colname="col2">Description 
					 </entry>
              </row>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
              <row>
                <entry colname="col1">
                  <p>Creative Cloud – Marketing Cloud 
						</p>
                </entry>
                <entry colname="col2">
                  <p>Marketing Cloud Users can now share folders to the
						  Creative Cloud and sync assets and comments across the two Clouds. See 
						  <xref href="https://marketing.adobe.com/resources/help/en_US/mcloud/?f=creative_cloud" format="https" scope="external">Share Marketing Cloud Folders and
