      <section id="fixes_reports_analytics">
        <title>Marketing Reports &amp; Analytics</title>
        <p>
          <b>Fixes</b>
        </p>
        <ul id="ul_581512B91CCE4B5989BD3235E6B8478C">
          <li id="li_1BB2EA4E25BE4CA4BCD12D3123BC30C1">
            <!--AN-91880-->Refined
				the way that visit and visitor metrics are calculated when only part of a visit
				is included in the selected reporting period, breakdown, or segment. After this
				change, if no measurable data for a metric is collected for the part of the
				visit that is included in the report, then a visit is not counted. 
				<b>This change will result in a small decrease in several metrics
				  including entries, exits, visits, visitors, single access, bounces, and visitor
				  home page</b>. For example, if a visit starts with a page view at 11:58pm on
				January 1, then ends with an exit link at 12:01am on January 2nd, a visit is
				not counted when reporting for the day of January 2nd only because a page view
				did not occur on that date. 
				<b>This change will also result in a small increase in Time Spent
				  Per Visit and Time Spent Per Visitor</b>, since a visit is no longer counted if
				there is not a value for time spent included in the calculation (since the last
				hit of a visit does not record time spent, if the report contains only the last
				hit due to filtering, a visit is no longer counted). 
			 </li>
          <li id="li_7551FD1C583346879614960F9A5728FC">
            <!--AN-86946-->Fixed an
				issue where deleted dashboards kept delivering weekly scheduled reports but
				were invisible in the Scheduled Reports Manager. 
			 </li>
          <li id="li_7B21BD842C8B43CC8610AE92E6B90DFA">
            <!--AN-91982-->Fixed an
				issue where customers were unable to download more than 50 lines of breakdown
				reports. 
			 </li>
          <li id="li_3D3818E3ED1A480E8CD9CCE57698E079">
            <!--AN-87891-->Fixed a
				browser cache issue that affected the visibility of segments in Internet
				Explorer 9. 
			 </li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          <xref href="01152015.xml#marketingcloud" format="dita" scope="local">Top</xref>
        </p>
