      <p>
        <xref href="01152015.xml#marketingcloud" format="dita" scope="local">Top</xref>
      </p>
      <p> See 
		  <xref href="https://marketing.adobe.com/resources/help/en_US/target/rn/" format="https" scope="external">Target Release Notes</xref> for the latest
		  information. 
		</p>
      <p>
        <b>
          <keyword>Recommendations</keyword>
        </b>
      </p>
      <p>Not updated in this release. 
		</p>
      <p>
        <xref href="01152015.xml#marketingcloud" format="dita" scope="local">Top</xref>
      </p>
      <section id="section_D28F5C0158D64702896CF29E3887E42A">
        <title>
          <keyword>Search&amp;Promote</keyword>
        </title>
        <p>
          <b>New feature</b>
        </p>
        <p>
          <ul id="ul_5D09AE7ACE744AAD941322FF77D88953">
            <li id="li_33A6D58A23704154BE2C890E33ABAFDE">
              <p>
                <!--3910450-->Previously, linguistics such as stemming, synonyms, and so forth,
				  were always applied to keywords in Guided Search rules. Now you can disable
				  this expansion so that the keyword is used as is. 
				</p>
              <p>When you want to apply trigger conditions to a Business Rule, in
				  the Advanced Rule Builder, following 
				  <uicontrol>If any/all of the following conditions are
					 met</uicontrol>, in the first drop-down list, select 
				  <uicontrol>keyword</uicontrol>, and then select the new operator 
				  <uicontrol>equal exact</uicontrol> in the second drop-down list. 
				</p>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </p>
        <p>
          <b>Fixed and enhancements</b>
        </p>
        <p>
          <ul id="ul_BA44227E37B64D8FA60154A85051B826">
            <li id="li_FC2535FEE3514DC8ADC7A84348AF246C">
              <p>
                <!--3178598-->Visual Rule Builder and Advanced Rule Builder no
				  longer truncates the MDI (Merchandising Document ID) field value. 
				</p>
            </li>
            <li id="li_1278EB720CF94AFFBE3FBFC91EAE411B">
              <p>
                <!--3803648-->RBTA-related indexing failures are now fixed. 
				</p>
            </li>
            <li id="li_80ECBF6417AD4D09AAAD8E7767C2D8FA">
              <p>
                <!--3841451-->Editing an existing Business Rule that has a
				  status of "approved" now revokes the "approved" status. You must use 
				  <wintitle>Advanced Rule Builder</wintitle> to recheck the option 
				  <uicontrol>Approved</uicontrol>, and then save the rule as usual.
				  If you do not reapprove an edited rule, the rule's status is automatically set
				  to WIP (Work In Progress) on the 
				  <wintitle>Business Rules</wintitle> page. 
				</p>
            </li>
            <li id="li_5B9B36058C0F404E976F0D01A7A09858">
              <p>
                <!--3841473-->A new 
				  <uicontrol>Advanced Search</uicontrol> option is now available on
				  the 
				  <wintitle>Business Rules</wintitle> page for improved filtering
				  of rules. 
				</p>
            </li>
            <li id="li_0ABECFB045B1476BAA71917276D59CF6">
              <p>
                <!--3841476-->Added 
				  <uicontrol>contains word</uicontrol> condition to rule triggers
				  in Query Cleaning, Pre-Search Rules, Post Search Rules, and Business Rules, to
				  let you easily specify word breaks. 
				</p>
            </li>
            <li id="li_C9459B5167F04C7698E21E9F051DAAA3">
              <p>
                <!--3841494-->Improvements made to Business Rule notes. For
				  example, you view a rule, you can now retrieve the notes history for that rule.
				  Also, notes are now logged in 
				  <uicontrol>Reports</uicontrol> &gt; 
				  <uicontrol>Change Log</uicontrol>. 
				</p>
            </li>
            <li id="li_7957A72A71F14950B3A2B641EB5579CD">
              <p>
                <!--3853568-->Queries with non-zero 
				  <codeph>sp_i</codeph> values are no longer run through the 
				  <keyword>SiteCatalyst</keyword> redirector. 
				</p>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </p>
        <p>
          <xref href="01152015.xml#marketingcloud" format="dita" scope="local">Top</xref>
        </p>
      </section>
    </conbody>
